# Stage Reader (The Reader — agentic Claude repo read) secrets — TEMPLATE
#
# Copy this file to ops/reader.local.env on the Pi and fill in the real token.
# The real file is GITIGNORED (matched by `*.local.env`) so the OAuth token never
# reaches the public repo. NEVER commit a token.
#
#     cp ops/reader.local.env.example ops/reader.local.env
#     chmod 600 ops/reader.local.env          # token is a secret; lock it down
#     # then edit ops/reader.local.env with the real token
#
# reader.js reads this file directly in Node (it never echoes the value) and
# passes ONLY this token — plus a scoped HOME/CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR and PATH — into
# the headless `claude` child. These are shell `KEY=value` lines, NOT a systemd
# unit. Do not add `[Service]`.

# --- Claude Code OAuth token (the Max-plan path) ----------------------------
# The Reader runs headless `claude` on Nick's Max subscription (zero marginal
# cost), NOT the metered Anthropic API. This token is what authorizes that path.
# Mint it on the Pi with:  claude setup-token   (it prints a token to paste here)
#
# COST SAFETY: do NOT set ANTHROPIC_API_KEY anywhere the server can see it. If an
# API key is present, it takes PRECEDENCE over this OAuth token and bills METERED
# per-token — a real ~$1,800 footgun. reader.js hard-aborts the run if it detects
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY in its environment rather than risk a silent metered bill.
CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=
